From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Luca Miccio <luca.miccio@amd.com>
Date: Sun, 27 Apr 2025 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Revert "drivers: firmware: xilinx: Add support to get the
 image uid info"

Partially reverts commit b75bf5f2d789.

The PDI sysfs interface requires dma_set_mask_and_coherent(32) which
fails in a Xen domU guest because guest physical memory is not
reachable with a 32-bit DMA mask.  The firmware driver does not
otherwise need DMA (it uses SMC calls), so removing the DMA mask
setup and the PDI sysfs entry allows versal2-firmware to probe in the
guest, unblocking the clock-controller and reset-controller needed by
the DisplayPort drivers.

Signed-off-by: Luca Miccio <luca.miccio@amd.com>
---
 drivers/firmware/xilinx/zynqmp-core.c | 13 -------------
 1 file changed, 13 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/firmware/xilinx/zynqmp-core.c b/drivers/firmware/xilinx/zynqmp-core.c
index 0977d351cbc4..62740d6d3cd1 100644
--- a/drivers/firmware/xilinx/zynqmp-core.c
+++ b/drivers/firmware/xilinx/zynqmp-core.c
@@ -897,12 +897,6 @@ static int zynqmp_firmware_probe(struct platform_device *pdev)
 		return ret;
 	}

-	ret = dma_set_mask_and_coherent(&pdev->dev, DMA_BIT_MASK(32));
-	if (ret < 0) {
-		dev_err(dev, "no usable DMA configuration");
-		return ret;
-	}
-
 	ret = zynqmp_firmware_pm_sysfs_entry(pdev);
 	if (ret) {
 		pr_err("%s() Failed to create sysfs file with error%d\n",
@@ -910,13 +904,6 @@ static int zynqmp_firmware_probe(struct platform_device *pdev)
 		return ret;
 	}

-	ret = zynqmp_firmware_pdi_sysfs_entry(pdev);
-	if (ret) {
-		pr_err("%s() Failed to create sysfs binary file with error%d\n",
-		       __func__, ret);
-		return ret;
-	}
-
 	zynqmp_pm_api_debugfs_init();

 	if (pm_family_code != PM_ZYNQMP_FAMILY_CODE) {
--
2.34.1
